Steps needed to reconstitute this repository as a real Codeshelf Cluster Master:

1. Find a set of machines (physical, virtual, cloud, whatever)
2. Set up master
	a. Create 'ansible' user (adduser ansible)
	b. Generate 'ansible' SSH keys (su ansible - ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096)
	c. Clone repository (cd /home/ansible; git clone git@github.com:codeshelf/Ansible-master.git master)
	d. Populate /home/ansible/.ssh/id_rsa.pub to root on the slave servers (manually, api's, whatever)
3. Fix roles/hosts/files/hosts if necessary
4. Fix inventory/site if necessary
5. Create group_vars/all from group_vars/all.sample
6. Run "spinup/configure.sh <slave_server>" for each slave
7. Create log directory (mkdir /home/ansible/master/log)
8. Fix key in roles/centos/files/ansible_authorized_keys
9. Put Java RPM into roles/java/files/java.rpm (cp jre-7u80-linux-x64.rpm /home/ansible/master/roles/java/files/java.rpm)
10. Add java key store to roles/fep/files/etc_codeshelf/codeshelfcom.signed.keystore.jks
11. Rsync into place Codeshelf code (rsync -avPt Codeshelf* /home/ansible/master/releases)
12. Create key repository (mkdir /home/ansible/ssl)
13. Make symlinks from roles/nginx/files/[certs,keys] to files in /home/ansible/ssl
14. Run Ansible (ansible-playbook site.yml) and get coffee

